    Tomato

Insert the correct property to make the text color violet.
    <p style="color: violet">This is a paragraph.</p>


The Alpha channel of a color controls the color-transparency, but which of the following values will be MOST transparent?
    background-color:rgba(255, 0, 0, 0);


What is the color of the following text: Hello (green)
    color:rgb(0, 255, 0)


Insert the correct RGB color values to make the background color completely blue.
    <p style="background-color:rgb(0, 0, 255)">This is a paragraph.</p>


Insert the a background color where green has the value 100, red has the value 106, and blue has the value 205.
    <p style="background-color:rgb(106, 100, 205)">This is a paragraph.</p


What is the highest HEX number of the following:
    a) #44
    b) #AA
    c) #BB
    > c

Insert the correct HEX value to make the text color white.
    <p style="color: #ffffff">This is a paragraph.</p>

Which one of the following will result in a grey color?
    a) #A0A0A0
    b) #FF00FF
    c) #00FF00
    > a


Which one of the following color values will result in a black color?
    a) hsl(0, 100%, 0%)
    b) hsl(0, 0, 100%)
    c) hsl(0, 100%, 100%)
    > a


Insert the HSLA value to make a color with no hue, 100% saturation, 50% lightness, and 50% transparency.
    <p style="color: hsla(0, 100%, 50%, 50%, 50%)">This is a paragraph.</p>

What does HSL stand for?
    a) HTML Signal Light
    b) Hue, Saturation and Lightness
    c) Higher Sense of Light
    > b